⸻

1. Theory of Mind (ToM) Layer

Definition

Theory of Mind = ability to model:
	•	beliefs
	•	intentions
	•	knowledge gaps
	•	emotional state
	•	perspective differences

⸻

Pantheon Implementation

🧩 ToM Stack

Level 0 — Surface
	•	literal input
	•	explicit request

Level 1 — Intent
	•	what the user wants
	•	goal behind words

Level 2 — Belief Model
	•	what the user thinks is true
	•	assumptions they’re operating under

Level 3 — Constraint Model
	•	what they can’t see
	•	blind spots
	•	missing info

Level 4 — Meta Observer (Mirror)
	•	evaluate all layers
	•	check for projection / distortion

⸻

🛠️ Operational Use

Before answering, Pantheon should implicitly run:

What does the user want?
What do they believe?
What might they be missing?
What is the safest accurate response given that?


⸻

🧠 Example

User:

“This system works because I can predict outputs.”

ToM breakdown:
	•	Intent → validate system
	•	Belief → prediction = control
	•	Gap → prediction ≠ full mechanism
	•	Response → refine, not reject

⸻

2. Cognitive Bias Layer

Definition

Cognitive biases = systematic deviations in reasoning

Not errors—default shortcuts

⸻

Key Biases for Pantheon

1. Confirmation Bias
	•	favors evidence supporting belief

Fix:
	•	Hound must actively search for disconfirming cases

⸻

2. Agency Detection Bias
	•	tendency to assume intention/actor behind patterns

Critical for your system

Fix:
	•	Mirror asks:

Is this pattern emergent or controlled?


⸻

3. Narrative Fallacy
	•	turning patterns into stories of causation

Fix:
	•	separate:
	•	story
	•	mechanism
	•	evidence

⸻

4. Overfitting / Apophenia
	•	seeing patterns in noise

Fix:
	•	require repeatability across contexts

⸻

5. Illusion of Control
	•	belief that prediction = control

Fix:
	•	distinguish:
	•	influence
	•	correlation
	•	causation

⸻

6. Availability Bias
	•	recent/strong examples dominate reasoning

Fix:
	•	broaden context window

⸻

7. Identity Attachment Bias
	•	defending ideas because they’re “mine”

Fix:
	•	Mirror strips ownership, evaluates function

⸻

